The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Life

 Busy beyond the boundary line

 ANUMITA GHOSH

 Cricketer Ajay Jadeja and model Sheena Chauhan sample the fare at Caught N Bowled, the newly-opened restaurant at City Centre by friends of Sourav Ganguly, prior to shooting for a commercial on Saturday; (above) cricketers Sanjay Bangar and Murali Kartik chill out at Souravs: The Food Pavilion on Sunday. Pictures by Rashbehari Das and Sanjoy Chattopadhyaya

 What: A Fun Fiesta with fashion, games, music and food.

 Where: Ordnance Club in Hastings.

 When: January 7 and 8.

 Model Anusmriti walks the ramp at a fashion show at Ordnance Club. Picture by Rashbehari Das

 The show: The two-day fun-filled event kicked off with a fashion show displaying creations of designers Kiran Dhanuka and Shruti Dhanuka of the label Aksh. Models flaunted an array of saris, salwar suits, westerns and lehngas. The salwar suits in crepes and georgettes were textured and printed and also embellished with appliques and sequin work. The motifs were largely floral. In lehngas, georgettes, raw silks and nets ruled the fabric fare. There was an assortment of the flowy kind with short cholis and also the A-line ones, co-ordinated with longish uppers.

 Dance performances by a local troupe between the fashion sequences, DJ Rahuls beat and a fancy dress competition added to the fun. 

 Sip n bite: The food stalls offered an assortment of idli, dosa, vegetable pakoras, jhalmuri, with sparkling apple juice to wash it down.

 Voiceover: The two-day event was all about fun and entertainment with food, music and dance, said club president Col M.K. Chaudhary.




